main event: Observers in Springer, New Mexico reported sighting multiple silvery white objects on April 25, 1949.
interesting points: The observed objects made a noise similar to ducks landing,The first group had 11 objects flying directly overhead at high speed,The second group of 9 followed shortly after from the East,The objects were in various formations,Some observers noted the objects were moving faster than sound.
witness description: Civilian observers, including a filling station employee and an ex-pilot
